<item>
            <title>[PIG-3510] New filter extractor fails with more than one filter statement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3510</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a regression from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3461&quot; title=&quot;Rewrite PartitionFilterOptimizer to make it work for all the cases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3461&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3461&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - rewrite of partition filter optimizer. Here is an example that demonstrates the problem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;two filters&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;b = FILTER a BY (dateint &amp;gt;= 20130901 AND dateint &amp;lt;= 20131001);
c = FILTER b BY (event_id == 419 OR event_id == 418);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;one filter&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;b = FILTER a BY (dateint &amp;gt;= 20130901 AND dateint &amp;lt;= 20131001) AND (event_id == 419 OR event_id == 418);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both dateint and event_id are partition columns. For the 1 filter case, the whole expression is pushed down whereas for the 2 filter case, only (event_id == 419 OR event_id == 418) is pushed down.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
